  "body": "# submission name:\nhenosis_qz_n3z_r25_clean\n\n# upload zipped `archive.zip`\n[archive.zip](https://github.com/henosis-us/comma_video_compression_challenge/raw/henosis_qz_n3z_r25_clean_submit/submissions/henosis_qz_n3z_r25_clean/archive.zip)\n\n# report.txt\n```\n=== Evaluation config ===\n  batch_size: 16\n  device: cuda\n  num_threads: 2\n  prefetch_queue_depth: 4\n  report: submissions/henosis_qz_n3z_r25_clean/report.txt\n  seed: 1234\n  submission_dir: submissions/henosis_qz_n3z_r25_clean\n  uncompressed_dir: /work/videos\n  video_names_file: /work/public_test_video_names.txt\n=== Evaluation results over 600 samples ===\n  Average PoseNet Distortion: 0.00035283\n  Average SegNet Distortion: 0.00070896\n  Submission file size: 284,425 bytes\n  Original uncompressed size: 37,545,489 bytes\n  Compression Rate: 0.00757548\n  Final score: 100*segnet_dist + sqrt(10*posenet_dist) + 25*rate = 0.32\n```\n\n# does your submission require gpu for evaluation (inflation)?\nyes\n\n# did you include the compression script? and want it to be merged?\nno\n\n# additional comments\nThis is a quantizr-derived, archive-counted submission. All submission-specific data needed for inflation is contained in `archive.zip` and counted in the reported archive size.\n\nLocal Linux CUDA/DALI evaluation reports a rounded score of `0.32`; the tracked exact local score is approximately `0.31968005`.\n",
